## Timeline of Key Events

| Year | Event |
|------|-------|
| 1962 | Born in Kowloon public housing |
| 1971 | Age 9: sees *The Big Boss*, wants to become Bruce Lee |
| 1983 | Joins TVB as extra; lands *430穿梭機* host role |
| 1988 | TV breakthrough *霹靂先鋒*; meets 吳孟達 |
| 1990 | *賭聖* — Hong Kong box office record |
| 1991 | *逃學威龍* — breaks own record |
| 1993 | *唐伯虎點秋香* — de facto directorial debut |
| 1994 | *國產凌凌漆* — first official directing credit |
| 1996 | *食神* — the spiritual autobiography of mastery |
| 1999 | *喜劇之王* — explicit autobiographical film; highest HK gross of year |
| 2001 | *少林足球* — international breakthrough; 7 HK Film Awards |
| 2004 | *功夫* — US$106M worldwide; top foreign-language film in North America |
| 2008 | *長江七號* — quietest film; poverty again, now with tenderness |
| 2010 | Split with girlfriend 于文鳳 after 12-year relationship |
| 2016 | *美人魚* — CN¥3.39B; all-time China record at the time |
| 2017 | 于文鳳 lawsuit (HK$130M claim) — settled privately |
| 2019 | *新喜劇之王* — the formula interrogated from inside |
| 2021 | 吳孟達 dies of liver cancer; Chow's response: four words |
| 2025 | Largely absent from public; Instagram presence only |

